    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of skull and lateral view of mandible of Thylogale billardierii (NMNH [Smithsonian Institution Museum of Natural History] # 582036) from Maria Island National Park, Tasmania. Greatest length of skull is 109.28 mm. Photograph by John Leeming of the Queen Victoria Museum, Launceston,Tasmania used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4573569/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

